    <title>Uniform Symbolic Topologies in Normal Toric Rings</title>
    <summary>  We show that all monomial prime ideals $P$ in a normal toric ring $R$ admit
uniform symbolic topologies, i.e., there is a uniform integer $D = D(R) &gt; 0$
such that the symbolic power $P^{(D N)} \subseteq P^N$ for all $N &gt;0$.
Moreover, we get sharp inclusions in this toric setting along the lines
proposed by Harbourne for graded ideals in polynomial rings. We compute $D$
explicitly in terms of basic data about the convex polyhedral cones used to
construct the ring.
</summary>
